{"id":"project-LICHEN-pfzz","title":"build.rs does not handle missing proto files gracefully","description":"File: rust/lichen-meshtastic/build.rs:6-18

The build.rs compiles proto files but will produce a cryptic error if any proto file is missing:

```rust
prost_build::Config::new().out_dir("src/").compile_protos(
    &[
        "proto/meshtastic/mesh.proto",
        "proto/meshtastic/portnums.proto",
        // ...
    ],
    &[proto_dir],
)?;
```

If a proto file is missing or the proto directory doesn't exist, prost_build returns an error, but the error message may not clearly indicate which file is missing.

Additionally, line 20:
```rust
println!("cargo:rerun-if-changed={}", proto_dir);
```

This only watches the proto directory, not individual proto files. If a proto file is deleted and the directory mtime doesn't change, the build might use stale generated code.

FIX OPTIONS:
1. Add explicit file existence checks with clear error messages
2. List each proto file for cargo:rerun-if-changed:
   ```rust
   for proto in &proto_files {
       println!("cargo:rerun-if-changed={}", proto);
   }
   ```","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:36:07.209853Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:36:07.209888Z"}

